 'AUTHOR-TITLE-ONLY', 'VERIFIED-2', 'https://www.dinmedia.de/en/standard/din-32975/122103522',
 '[session_2026-07-19-non-english-research-recovery-batch4] WebFetch non-functional this session (DIN Media, Beuth, standard.no, and ~15 unrelated domains all 403''d, confirmed session-wide tooling issue). Verified via 3+ independent secondary specialist sources (nullbarriere.de -- a well-known German accessibility/DIN-standards reference site; a Bavarian government accessibility-office blog; baunormenlexikon.de) agreeing on title, edition, and the K=0.4/0.7/0.8 threshold structure. "Handrails" attribution to the K>=0.4 tier specifically could not be independently confirmed (floor markings/orientation elements are the consistently-cited K>=0.4 category; handrail contrast is more prominently specified in DIN 32984/related guidance referencing these DIN 32975 values) -- not asserted here beyond what was confirmed.',
