 2019, 'DGUV Information 207-027 — Neu- und Umbauplanung im Krankenhaus unter Gesichtspunkten des Arbeitsschutzes – Anforderungen an Pflegebereiche',
 'DGUV', 'de', 'de', 'manual_native_language_verification',
 5, 'national_fw', 'DE', 'DGUV Information 207-027 (01/2019)',
 'AUTHOR-TITLE-ONLY', 'VERIFIED-2', 'https://kuvb.de/fileadmin/daten/dokumente/GBI/Gesundheitsdienst/DGUV_Information_207-027__Neu-_und_Umbauplanung_im_Krankenhaus_-_Pflegebereiche_.pdf',
 '[session_2026-07-19-non-english-research-recovery-batch4] FRESH RESEARCH (PRE-REMEDIATION-stub slug). WebFetch non-functional this session. Verified via multiple independent statutory-accident-insurer mirror sites (kuvb.de, unfallkasse-nrw.de) hosting the identical document with matching title/number/edition, plus the public "Sicheres Krankenhaus" interpretive portal (jointly published by BGW and Unfallkasse NRW) which republishes this series with dedicated pages for psychiatric/forensic-psychiatric wards -- content details (glazing thickness, flooring class) recurred consistently across independent queries.',
 'Fresh-research recovery per research-handoff-non-english.md, extended to a PRE-REMEDIATION-stub slug (mental-health-built-environment, DE).',
 'National occupational-safety-oriented hospital-planning standard with a dedicated section on closed psychiatric wards (geschlossene psychiatrische Stationen): vandalism-resistant supply-line routing, entrance airlocks/vestibules with lockable storage for prohibited items, hazard-analysis-driven window/door/glazing resistance (4mm polycarbonate interior glazing, 6mm for forensic units), slip-resistant flooring (R10/R11 class) in wet areas, sound insulation and blackout provisions, color-design recommendations.',
 strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ','now'), 'session_2026-07-19-non-english-research-recovery-batch4', strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ','now'), 'session_2026-07-19-non-english-research-recovery-batch4'),

('REF-00762', 'book', 4, 1, 0, 'van Mierlo T, Bovenberg F, Voskes Y, Mulder N',
 2013, 'Werkboek HIC: High en Intensive Care in de Psychiatrie',
 'De Tijdstroom / Boom uitgevers', 'nl', 'nl', 'manual_native_language_verification',
 3, 'grey', 'NL', 'ISBN 978-90-5898-235-3',
 'AUTHOR-TITLE-ONLY', 'VERIFIED-2', 'https://www.tijdschriftvoorpsychiatrie.nl/issues/478/articles/10309',
 '[session_2026-07-19-non-english-research-recovery-batch4] FRESH RESEARCH (PRE-REMEDIATION-stub slug). WebFetch non-functional this session. Verified via a Tijdschrift voor Psychiatrie review, publisher page (boom.nl), and independent project descriptions (e.g. GGz Breburg implementation) corroborating authors/ISBN/publisher/originating field initiative. The underlying "HIC-monitor" audit instrument has been validated across 21 Dutch institutions/38 audits (VUmc research, 2014-2015) and is now the de facto national practice standard for acute/intensive psychiatric admission units -- field-developed, not government-mandated, but nationally adopted. Specific room-layout detail is drawn from secondary project descriptions, not the primary text (which could not be directly fetched).',
 'Fresh-research recovery per research-handoff-non-english.md, extended to a PRE-REMEDIATION-stub slug (mental-health-built-environment, NL). A second NL candidate (College bouw zorginstellingen "Referentiekader bestaande bouw AWBZ") was investigated and found to be a defunct/historical national standard (the issuing body was dissolved ~2009 when Dutch healthcare-building financing moved to a market-based system) -- not ingested, since citing it as current guidance would be misleading; flagged in the coverage matrix instead.',
 'The HIC-monitor quality instrument (built on this workbook) includes "ruimtelijke vormgeving" (spatial/architectural design) as one of ten quality dimensions: avoiding corners/niches to maintain staff sightlines, central staff positioning with unit-wide overview, three graduated security levels within a unit (High Care / Intensive Care / extra-secure EBK rooms), calming color schemes, cleanable flooring, non-institutional park-like building appearance.',
 strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ','now'), 'session_2026-07-19-non-english-research-recovery-batch4', strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ','now'), 'session_2026-07-19-non-english-research-recovery-batch4');

